          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Gregoire Pichon",
          "email": "gregoire.pichon@bull.net",
          "date": "2015-03-17 15:28:24.000000000",
          "tz": 60
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2015-04-06 01:05:33.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-5319 ptlrpc: Add a tag field to ptlrpc messages",
        "message": "LU-5319 ptlrpc: Add a tag field to ptlrpc messages\n\nThe new tag field is used as a virtual index for multiple modifying\nRPCs management. It is set by the client and allows the target to\nrelease in-memory reply data when the tag is reused by a new RPC.\n\nThe tag field replaces the unused last_seen field of ptlrpcd_body\nstructure.\n\nAdditionally, the last_xid field is used to transfer the highest XID\nfor which a reply has been received and does not have an unreplied\nlower-numbered XID.\n\nSigned-off-by: Gregoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nChange-Id: I4a57f3710ffffe21d8d655af6ac222b65051a12d\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/14095\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Alex Zhuravlev <alexey.zhuravlev@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
